International Relations and Cooperations Minister Lindiwe Sisulu will personally apologise to Lesotho King Letsie III after he was allegedly “mistreated” at the border gates between the two countries. King Letsie III was allegedly held for hours at the Maseru Bridge border post while his convoy was also searched. The king was unhappy with in the manner in which he was treated. The minister is expected to travel to Lesotho to personally extend an apology to him. Sisulu said that although she had already apologised to the king, she would also go to Lesotho to meet him. “I have extended through him, my sincerest apologies for this and I have indicated to him that I will personally go to Lesotho to apologise to the king for any mistreatment he might have encountered at our border,” Sisulu said. -TNA Reporter